init_text:
What Stereotypical Characters Make You Cringe?

What stereotypical characters in books, movies or television shows make you cringe and why? Would you ever not watch or read something because of its offensive portrayal of someone?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: the most offensive stereotype is the portrayal of Native Americans.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I have seen many movies and read many books where the Native Americans are portrayed as savages, uncivilized, and/or unintelligent.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I have also seen many movies and read many books where the Native Americans are portrayed as wise, spiritual, and/or mystical.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are often shown as the "keepers of the earth" or the "keepers of the balance."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They are often shown as the "keepers of the ancient wisdom."

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: There were also periods of time where tribes would treat their enemies with respect and kindness.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: Recent movies such as "Twilight" still rely on  stereotypes, even in this decade.
